<item>
            <title>[LU-12372] Look at increasing OST_MAXREQSIZE</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12372</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently,&#160;OST_MAXREQSIZE is limited to 16 KiB.&#160; This limits the upper size of short i/o (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1757&quot; title=&quot;Short I/O support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1757&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1757&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) to this size.&#160; This ticket is to examine the implications of growing this limit, to, for example, 64 KiB - The concern is if we end up allocating the larger buffer size all the time for certain operations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Basically, we/I need to examine the code to see if this is the case, and if it&apos;s not, we should look at increasing the upper limit, at least to see if it has a positive impact.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="55817">LU-12372</key>
            <summary>Look at increasing OST_MAXREQSIZE</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11303&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
